 Port Elizabeth - The South African National Roads Agency SOC Ltd (SANRAL) would like to notify travellers that roadworks are in progress on Standford Road Bridge and the N2 Freeway in Port Elizabeth. On Tuesday, 17 September, from 7pm and mid-night the freeway carriage way will be closed for road markings. There will be a change in road lane markings to deviate traffic slightly to the right approaching Standford Bridge from Cotswold side. The deviation will divert traffic 1,5m to the right for 140meters and then back on existing lanes. “We urge motorists to please adhere to the reduced speed limit,” Mbulelo Peterson, SANRAL Southern Region Manager said. SANRAL apologises for any inconvenience caused. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 